New Records: Saud Shakeel and Mohammad Rizwan brought up their 100-run partnership in the 25th over, the second-fastest fifty for Pakistan in the history of the Men's Cricket World Cup
Key Match Events: Scott Edwards dismissed Saud Shakeel in the 24th over
Haris Rauf's double-wicket over in the 34th over brought the game back into Pakistan's side
Bas de Leede scored 67 from 68, hitting six fours and two sixes during his innings
Mohammed Rizwan was dismissed by Bas de Leede in the 32nd over
Saqib Zulfiqar caught Saud Shakeel at mid-wicket in the 29th over
Pre-Game Insights: Scott Edwards called it right at the toss and the Dutch opted to field against Babar Azam's Pakistan
Netherlands have a perfect head-to-head record of 6-0 over Netherlands in the ODI format
Miscellaneous Highlights: Left-handed batter Vikramjit provided Netherlands a stable start
The fourth wicket pair of Rizwan and Shakeel adopted an attacking policy to get the innings going once again
Fakhar Zaman and Imam-ul-Haq found the going tough on a surface where the ball was holding its line on occasions and taking turn on other
